A few words, if I may. To anyone and everyone joining this game: Please make sure that you do have time to commit to the game. Recently, activity on the site hasn't been at its best. I'm pretty sure there are more than one reasons for this, but one of them (for sure) has to do with players who join the game and then regret joining because they can't keep up, or miscalculated the time they could commit to the game, etc. I know a lot of people playing on this site are competent players, and a lot of new players are showing promise in their capabilities. But if you can't commit (or have a feeling that you won't be able) to a game that might run for over a week, or are planning to lurk and contribute to the lack of activity, please leave the game while you still can. If you join the game, then please make sure you really can commit some serious time into it.

To the newbies: I'd personally advise to only join this game if you have a lot of experience with wlf games, or even played 2 or 3 exts (and actively participated in them). Same thing applies to you guys. In the game we're all anonymous, so claiming that you're new isn't going to win you any favours, or could even be seen as you trying to hide as a potential evil. If you're playing in the site for the first time and have joined this game, I'd suggest you wait for a wlf lobby to be open and join that game, as this setup is expected to be very complicated.
Looks like wlf-076 is open for sign-up, so those who're playing for the first time (or are not as experienced with games), I'd suggest you go over to that lobby.
Apologies if I come off as harsh/condescending in any way, but I really want to make sure that this ext doesn't suffer from inactivity like the last few games did.
Especially this one. And I hope that this game can change the trend of inactivity for the upcoming games.
